# UI002 — ui_no_raw_variant
#
# Lint rule: flag string literals in known variant positions:
#   - with_on_typed_action(node, "<literal>") — action name should be typed
#   - toast(id, message, "<literal>")         — variant should be typed
#
# Implementation lives in:
#   src/compiler/90.tools/lint/main.spl — Linter.check_ui_raw_variant()
#
# Rule logic summary:
#   - For with_on_typed_action: parse second arg; if starts with `"` → UI002
#   - For toast: parse third arg; if starts with `"` → UI002
#
# Allowlisted paths (never flagged):
#   common/ui/builder.spl       — defines with_on_action (legacy wrapper)
#   common/ui/glass/builder.spl — defines toast()
#
# Note: with_on_action(node, handler_id: text) is a lifecycle handler ID,
#       not an action name. That function is NOT flagged — only with_on_typed_action
#       with a string literal second arg is flagged, as that would be misuse.
#
# Suggested fixes:
#   with_on_typed_action → use CommonAction.Save.into_action() or Action.Custom(name: "...")
#   toast variant         → use a typed constant once StatusVariant lands
#
# Registration: compiler.tools.lint.main.{all_lint_names, build_default_levels,
#               map_lint_code_to_config_name, Linter.new, Linter.lint_source}
